This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the problem of machine translation. Additionally, the use of word alignment algorithms and dictionaries suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Natural Language Processing (cs.NE). The use of neural networks in the proposed technique makes it relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of translation tasks and the potential application of the proposed technique to image captioning tasks suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV).
